	(44747,1539,'content_ml_rich_text_english','<ul>\n<li><blockquote>\n<p>Conduct remote monitoring and assessment of the situation in Xinjiang and report publicly on the situation, in line with the independent mandate provided by General Assembly resolution 48/141, with concrete recommendations for next steps.</p>\n</blockquote></li>\n<li><blockquote>\n<p>Brief the Human Rights Council on the situation as a matter of urgency, in line with HRC resolution 45/31, which clearly requested that the High Commissioner bring information concerning “patterns of human rights violations that point to a heightened risk of a human rights emergency… to the attention of the members and observers of the Human Rights Council in a manner that reflects the urgency of the situation… including through briefings.”</p>\n</blockquote></li>\n</ul>'),
