	(47644,1619,'quote_or_personal_detail_ml_rich_text_basic_english','Sadir has been the owner of a real estate company since 2015 and is described by his daughter as very religious, quiet, hard-working and attached to his family. She added: “He spent all his time with family. He paid for my studies, my living, [my and my sister’s] school. He has been working all the time.” \nOther family members have unfortunately also been detained. The uncle of Sadir’s wife, [Abiden Eyyubhaji](#case-SR020), a 91-year-old religious scholar, was reportedly sent to an internment camp in 2016, and one of his wife’s cousins, [Yusupjan Abiden](#case-SR030), a 55-year-old former religious teacher at the Islamic Scripture College of Xinjiang in Urumqi, is in prison since 2017.'),
