	(47772,1620,'summary',''),
	(47773,1620,'_summary','field_6037389d32918'),
	(47774,1620,'quote_or_personal_detail_ml_rich_text_basic_english','Suppiyem, now about 60 years old, is a hard-working woman who often travelled on business. She owns a shop selling clothes, hats and assorted items in Shahyar. Her granddaughter remembers her as always busy with family and business, adding: “She didn’t have an easy life.” She also recalls her grandmother’s surprise when she saw how people could talk without restrictions in Turkey. “She [Suppiyem] was saying, ‘Oh, you can speak so loud here, so freely here.’ She wasn’t used to it.”\nOne of Suppiyem’s daughters, [Hepisem Mehmet](#case-SR021), also went missing after the same trip to Turkey and might have been sent to an internment camp sometime between 2016 and 2017.'),
