	(49334,1632,'quote_or_personal_detail_ml_rich_text_basic_english','Yusupjan is a former religious teacher who later became a businessman. The family members that Amnesty International interviewed remember him as very respected, loved by his students and particularly helpful towards others. \nThey also added that he is married and has one son and two daughters, and that his wife spent two years in an internment camp. \nOther family members have also been detained: [Sadir Ali](#case-SR016), sent to prison probably in May 2019 with a 20-year sentence, and [Abiden Eyyubhaji](#case-SR020) has reportedly been held in an internment camp since 2017.'),
