	(52054,1653,'summary_ml_rich_text_basic_english','Abdurishid’s daughter told Amnesty International that Abdurishid, a restaurant owner from Artux County, was taken away in December 2017. His daughter, currently living in Turkey, thinks that he has been held in an internment facility for allegedly sending money to family members in Egypt. \nBefore being detained, Abdurishid asked his daughter not to return to China when she was at university on a Turkish scholarship programme. Her father told her that people who went abroad were experiencing some problems in China, and he gradually removed their contact and accounts on WeChat.\nAbdurishid’s oldest son, [Rizayidin Abdurishid](#case-SR058), is also in a detention facility.'),
